column1: Is the pest in the image an armyworm?
column2: Is the armyworm green in color?
column3: Is the armyworm brown in color?
column4: Is the armyworm found on the leaf top?
column5: Is the armyworm found on the underside of the leaf?
column6: Is the armyworm present on the stem?
column7: Is the armyworm feeding on the crop?
column8: Are visible bite marks present on the leaf?
column9: Are there multiple armyworms in the image?
column10: Is any frass (armyworm waste) visible near the pest?
column11: Are eggs visible near the armyworm?
column12: Are larvae of the armyworm visible?
column13: Has the crop been attacked by armyworm in previous seasons?
column14: Was pesticide recently applied to this crop area?
column16: Is the armyworm active during daylight hours?
column17: Is the armyworm mostly active during night?
column18: Is the leaf portion of the plant affected?
column19: Is the stem portion of the plant affected?
column20: Is the damage restricted to a small part of the crop?
column21: Are nearby plants also showing signs of armyworm infestation?
column23: Are there signs of curled leaves due to feeding?
column24: Has the armyworm damaged more than one section of the same plant?
column25: Is there visible discoloration of the crop due to pest feeding?
column26: Does the armyworm show striping or lines on its body?
column27: Is the length of the armyworm greater than 20 mm?
column28: Are any dead armyworms seen in the area (possibly due to pesticide)?
column29: Is any chewing sound audible during the inspection?
column30: Has any farmer nearby reported armyworm infestation in the last week?
